"title": "9250: woe",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9250",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An exclamation of judgment upon God's enemies, or of misfortune on oneself, or, in the ministry of Jesus Christ, of sadness over those who fail to recognise the true misery of their condition.</p>\n<h2>Woe as an exclamation of judgment on others</h2>\n<h3>Woe to God's enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:1\">ISA 33:1</a></strong> <em>Probably referring to Assyria.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:1-Jer48:2\">JER 48:1–48:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:1-Nah3:7\">NAM 3:1–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:6-Hab2:20\">HAB 2:6–2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:5\">ZEP 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to God's faithless people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:13-Hos7:16\">HOS 7:13–7:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9-Isa45:10\">ISA 45:9–45:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:13-Jer4:18\">JER 4:13–4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:23-Ezek16:27\">EZK 16:23–16:27</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to careless leaders of God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:1-Jer23:2\">JER 23:1–23:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:1-Ezek13:9\">EZK 13:1–13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:1-Ezek34:10\">EZK 34:1–34:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:1-Zeph3:4\">ZEP 3:1–3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:15-Zech11:17\">ZEC 11:15–11:17</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to those who are complacent in their prosperity or religion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:1-Amos6:7\">AMO 6:1–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:24\">AMO 5:18–5:24</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to those who neglect social justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:4\">ISA 10:1–10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:8-Isa5:23\">ISA 5:8–5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13-Jer22:19\">JER 22:13–22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:1-Mic2:3\">MIC 2:1–2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to a godless world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:13\">REV 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:12\">REV 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:10\">REV 18:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:16-Rev18:17\">REV 18:16–18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:19\">REV 18:19</a></p>\n<h2>Woe as an exclamation of misfortune on oneself</h2>\n<h3>Woe as a consequence of circumstances or events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:19\">JER 10:19</a></strong> <em>Jeremiah is describing the pain he feels at the impending destruction of his nation.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:6-1Sam4:8\">1SA 4:6–4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps120:5-Ps120:7\">PSA 120:5–120:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:13\">JER 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Woe as a consequence of one's own sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:16\">LAM 5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:8-Isa3:9\">ISA 3:8–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5\">ISA 6:5</a></p>\n<h3>Woe as a consequence of God's call on one's life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:16\">1CO 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer45:1-Jer45:5\">JER 45:1–45:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:9-Ezek3:11\">EZK 2:9–3:11</a></p>\n<h2>Woe as an exclamation of sadness over others</h2>\n<h3>Woe to those who do not recognise their own needs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:24-Luke6:26\">LUK 6:24–6:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Woe to those whose religion blinds themselves and misleads others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:52\">LUK 11:52</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:13-Matt23:33\">MAT 23:13–23:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:42-Luke11:51\">LUK 11:42–11:51</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to those who cause others to sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:7\">MAT 18:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:1-Luke17:3\">LUK 17:1–17:3</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to those on whom judgment is coming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:13-Luke10:14\">LUK 10:13–10:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:20-Matt11:22\">MAT 11:20–11:22</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to the one who betrays the Son of Man</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:24\">MAT 26:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:21\">MRK 14:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:22\">LUK 22:22</a></p>\n<h3>Woe to those who experience the signs of the end of the age</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:19-Matt24:21\">MAT 24:19–24:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:17-Mark13:19\">MRK 13:17–13:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:23\">LUK 21:23</a> <em>The word translated “how dreadful” is the same word that elsewhere is translated “woe”.</em></p>\n<h2>Woe may give way to forgiveness, comfort and deliverance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5-Isa6:7\">ISA 6:5–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:1-Isa29:8\">ISA 29:1–29:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:1-Isa40:2\">ISA 40:1–40:2</a> <em>After the woes of earlier chapters, Isaiah now prophesies the comfort that will come to God's people</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer45:2-Jer45:5\">JER 45:2–45:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:16-Lam3:26\">LAM 3:16–3:26</a></p>",
